reviews.review_text:
Great sound, fun show !  Track list is wrong. Thanks for sharing and posting.  But it looks like including the Baby Blue encore after set 1 threw the whole track list off one in set II. 

i.e. Scarlet is labelled Fire, Fire labelled Playin', etc.

Doesn't affect the enjoyment at all but it had me scratching my head for a minute.
Heavy questions How many frickin over the top great Sugarees are on this site?  Will I ever time of them?  SMOKIN

Great sound, mislabeled tracks This really has exceptional sound especially for an audience tape, but I had to dock it a couple stars for being incomplete.  

Also, the track labels go all awry once the first set ends - those are all correct.  The encore (Baby Blue) was moved to the end of the first set, but its label reads Scarlet Bogonias.  So all the track names from then on - are off by one.  Just making people aware.  Not hard to fix, but the issue is there.

Not to dis this, but this tours Boards deserve airing I amnot buying the $700 thing, but I deserve the best copy there is of 10/12/84, because for me and my friends its a big deal, as it twas our twelfth and twentieh etc shows or something and now that we have been to 200 or so we liked that one, we actually always visit theAugusta Civic center when we drive by, last time it was a gun show and it looked smalleer than my garage. Anyways bring out your boards for this tour please..............shnip, and see u at something called 11/7/15, whateverthat is
In the Dark Great show, excellent AUD.  Was this tagged in the dark??

Great First Set, Set 2 so so Really Great 1st set. jack Straw loses focus a bit. Sugaree among the best ever. Bobby was going crazy with his new wammy bar the whole tour, sometimes delightfully. Check out the Bird Song and how Jerry is led so nicely by Bobby's awesome rhythm playing!
  Set 2 Scarlet Fire meanders etc.

Fully Warmed Up Fall tour started on 10/5 with a few bumpy shows leading up to 10/15.  Jerry really going for the gusto on Playing, this is a must spin 84 show.

Highlights:  Playing In The Band, Space, The Wheel

What a night! Woah! 

Is this the best Jack/Job ever??

I have never heard one more on fire. Bobby & Jerry are cooking throughout!!
